The paper proposes a SLAM system for UAVs using depth prediction with Capsule Networks, which is a combination of computer vision, robotics, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves computer vision techniques such as CNNs and CapsNet, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the second likely sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms such as CapsNet and Extended Kalman Filter indicates cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves AI techniques such as SLAM and belief updating, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves control and estimation techniques such as the Extended Kalman Filter, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the fifth likely sub-category.
